Key Match Events: Austin Riley hit a two-run homer
Post-Match Reflections: The Braves players danced in a mob near the mound as Phillies fans booed them off the field
Braves manager Brian Snitker said, 'We’ve checked one box'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Braves clinched their sixth straight NL East title
The Braves have seemingly made winning the East a rite of September since the 1990s
The Braves took special satisfaction in clinching on the same Citizens Bank Park field where the Phillies eliminated them last October in the NL Division Series
Others: Kirby Yates struck out Brandon Marsh to end the game
Kevin Pillar added an RBI double in the fourth for a 4-1 lead
Cristopher Sánchez struck out a career-best 10 in 7 1/3 innings
